message: "If you use or adapt this work, please cite it as below."
type: report
title: "Agentic SAMM: An OWASP SAMM Extension for AI-Driven Development"
authors:
  - family-names: Gordeychik
    given-names: Sergey
    email: scadastrangelove@gmail.com
    affiliation: CyberOK
date-released: 2026
version: "0.2.0-draft"
license: CC-BY-SA-4.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/scadastrangelove/asamm"
abstract: >
  Agentic SAMM extends OWASP SAMM to systems where software is no longer
  the only actor. It provides a threat taxonomy, migration and greenfield
  adoption paths, 19 controls across five SAMM function families, and a
  structured audit methodology with three audit tracks for teams building
  or securing AI-driven development systems.
keywords:
  - agentic AI
  - secure SDLC
  - OWASP SAMM
  - application security
  - AI security
  - prompt injection
  - tool abuse
  - autonomous agents
